<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    <p class="intro">Everything you need to know about SciFigure Pro. Can't find the answer? <a href="mailto:support@scifigure.pro">Contact our support team</a>.</p>
    
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="question">Q: How much does SciFigure Pro cost?</div>
        <div class="answer">
          <div class="answer-summary"><strong>Answer:</strong> SciFigure Pro offers flexible pricing: Free tier (3 figures/month), Pro Plan ($9.99/month), Team Plan ($24.99/month per user). Annual billing saves 20%.</div>
          <details>
            <summary>Read full answer</summary>
            <div class="answer-full">
              <p><strong>Free Tier:</strong> 3 figures/month, basic export formats (PNG, JPG), community support, watermark on exports.</p>
              <p><strong>Pro Plan - $9.99/month:</strong> Unlimited figures, all export formats (TIFF, PNG, SVG, PDF), priority support, no watermark, batch processing.</p>
              <p><strong>Team Plan - $24.99/month per user:</strong> Everything in Pro, plus shared templates, team libraries, collaboration features, API access, dedicated support.</p>
              <p><strong>Enterprise:</strong> Custom pricing for labs with 10+ users. Contact us for a quote.</p>
              <p>All plans include a 14-day free trial of Pro features. No credit card required for free tier.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="question">Q: What figure formats does SciFigure Pro support?</div>
        <div class="answer">
          <div class="answer-summary"><strong>Answer:</strong> SciFigure Pro supports all major scientific image formats: PNG, TIFF, JPG, SVG, EPS, PDF for input; TIFF, PNG, SVG, PDF for output.</div>
          <details>
            <summary>Read full answer</summary>
            <div class="answer-full">
              <p><strong>Input Formats:</strong> PNG, TIFF, JPG/JPEG, SVG, EPS, PDF, BMP, GIF (we recommend PNG or TIFF for best quality).</p>
              <p><strong>Output Formats:</strong></p>
              <ul>
                <li>TIFF (journal-ready, 300 DPI, CMYK/RGB)</li>
                <li>PNG (presentation-ready, transparent background option)</li>
                <li>SVG (editable in Illustrator/Inkscape)</li>
                <li>PDF (print-ready, vector-based)</li>
              </ul>
              <p><strong>Automatic Optimization:</strong> All outputs are automatically optimized for journal requirements (300 DPI minimum, correct color mode, proper dimensions).</p>
              <p><strong>Batch Conversion:</strong> Convert 10+ figures to the same format in one click.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="question">Q: How do I get started with SciFigure Pro?</div>
        <div class="answer">
          <div class="answer-summary"><strong>Answer:</strong> Getting started takes less than 2 minutes: Sign up at scifigure.pro, upload your figures, select your target journal, click 'Format'.</div>
          <details>
            <summary>Read full answer</summary>
            <div class="answer-full">
              <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Sign up for free at <a href="https://scifigure.pro">scifigure.pro</a>. No credit card required.</p>
              <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Upload your figure images (drag-and-drop or click to browse).</p>
              <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Select your target journal (or use our generic template).</p>
              <p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Click "Format" - your figures are ready in seconds!</p>
              <p><strong>No Installation:</strong> Everything runs in your browser. Works on Windows, Mac, Linux, iPad.</p>
              <p><strong>Free Trial:</strong> Try all Pro features free for 14 days.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="question">Q: Is SciFigure Pro compatible with my workflow?</div>
        <div class="answer"><div class="warning" style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #ffc107; margin: 10px 0;"><strong>⚠️ Note:</strong> This feature is coming soon (expected in next release).</div>
          <div class="answer-summary"><strong>Answer:</strong> Yes! SciFigure Pro integrates seamlessly with ImageJ/Fiji, GraphPad Prism, Photoshop, Illustrator. Supports copy-paste, drag-and-drop, batch processing.</div>
          <details>
            <summary>Read full answer</summary>
            <div class="answer-full">
              <p><strong>Compatible with:</strong></p>
              <ul>
                <li>ImageJ/Fiji (export as TIFF/PNG)</li>
                <li>GraphPad Prism (export graphs as images)</li>
                <li>Photoshop (import/export)</li>
                <li>Illustrator (SVG export for further editing)</li>
                <li>OriginLab, MATLAB, Python (matplotlib)</li>
              </ul>
              <p><strong>Integration Features:</strong></p>
              <ul>
                <li>Simple copy-paste from clipboard</li>
                <li>Drag-and-drop interface</li>
                <li>Batch processing (format 10+ figures at once)</li>
                <li>API access (Team plan) for custom workflows</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="question">Q: Is my data secure with SciFigure Pro?</div>
        <div class="answer">
          <div class="answer-summary"><strong>Answer:</strong> Data security is our top priority: AES-256 encryption, no storage of your figures, GDPR compliant, you retain 100% ownership.</div>
          <details>
            <summary>Read full answer</summary>
            <div class="answer-full">
              <p><strong>Encryption:</strong> All uploads are encrypted with AES-256 during transfer and processing.</p>
              <p><strong>No Storage:</strong> Your figures are processed in memory and permanently deleted immediately after you download. We never store your raw data.</p>
              <p><strong>No Training:</strong> We never use your figures to train AI models. Your data is never shared with third parties.</p>
              <p><strong>GDPR Compliant:</strong> Full data processing agreement available. You have the right to request deletion of any metadata.</p>
              <p><strong>Ownership:</strong> You retain 100% ownership of your figures. We claim no rights to your intellectual property.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="question">Q: Can I export figures for specific journals?</div>
        <div class="answer">
          <div class="answer-summary"><strong>Answer:</strong> Absolutely! Built-in templates for 200+ journals (Nature, Science, Cell, PNAS, Elsevier, Springer, IEEE, ACM). Each template automatically adjusts dimensions, resolution, color mode, font, label style.</div>
          <details>
            <summary>Read full answer</summary>
            <div class="answer-full">
              <p><strong>Supported Journals:</strong> Nature, Science, Cell, PNAS, all Elsevier journals, all Springer journals, IEEE, ACM, and 200+ more.</p>
              <p><strong>Automatic Adjustments:</strong></p>
              <ul>
                <li>Dimensions (width/height in mm or inches)</li>
                <li>Resolution (300 DPI minimum)</li>
                <li>Color mode (CMYK for print, RGB for online)</li>
                <li>Font requirements (Arial, Helvetica, Times)</li>
                <li>Label style (A, B, C...)</li>
              </ul>
              <p><strong>Custom Templates:</strong> Can't find your journal? Use our custom template creator to specify your own requirements.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="question">Q: Does SciFigure Pro work on mobile devices?</div>
        <div class="answer">
          <div class="answer-summary"><strong>Answer:</strong> SciFigure Pro is fully responsive: Works on desktop (Windows, Mac, Linux), tablet (iPad, Android), mobile (iOS, Android) for viewing and downloading.</div>
          <details>
            <summary>Read full answer</summary>
            <div class="answer-full">
              <p><strong>Desktop (Recommended):</strong> Full editing capabilities, batch processing, all features available.</p>
              <p><strong>Tablet:</strong> Full editing capabilities, touch-optimized interface.</p>
              <p><strong>Mobile:</strong> View and download formatted figures, share with collaborators. Editing is limited on small screens (we recommend desktop for creating figures).</p>
              <p><strong>Offline Mode:</strong> Not currently supported (figures are processed in the cloud for best performance). We're working on a desktop app with offline capabilities.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="question">Q: How accurate is the AI resolution enhancement?</div>
        <div class="answer">
          <div class="answer-summary"><strong>Answer:</strong> Our AI resolution enhancement is highly accurate (95%+ perceptual quality). Uses deep learning super-resolution (ESRGAN architecture). Best for blurry photos, low-res screenshots, older figures.</div>
          <details>
            <summary>Read full answer</summary>
            <div class="answer-full">
              <p><strong>Technology:</strong> Uses deep learning super-resolution (ESRGAN architecture) trained on 1M+ scientific images.</p>
              <p><strong>Accuracy:</strong> 95%+ perceptual quality (tested against expert ratings). The AI enhances details that are already present but blurry.</p>
              <p><strong>Best For:</strong> Blurry photos, low-res screenshots, older figures that need updating.</p>
              <p><strong>Limitations:</strong> Cannot recover lost detail (garbage in = garbage out). Not recommended for raw data images (use original instead).</p>
              <p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Always keep your original highest-resolution files as backup. AI enhancement is great, but nothing beats the original high-res file.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="question">Q: What kind of support does SciFigure Pro offer?</div>
        <div class="answer">
          <div class="answer-summary"><strong>Answer:</strong> Comprehensive support: step-by-step guides, video tutorials, email support (24h response), priority support (Team plan), user forum, custom requests.</div>
          <details>
            <summary>Read full answer</summary>
            <div class="answer-full">
              <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> Step-by-step guides, video tutorials, journal templates, FAQ.</p>
              <p><strong>Email Support:</strong> Response within 24 hours (free for all users).</p>
              <p><strong>Priority Support:</strong> Dedicated scientist support (Team plan) with 4-hour response time.</p>
              <p><strong>Community:</strong> User forum, feature requests, tips sharing.</p>
              <p><strong>Custom Requests:</strong> Journal template requests (free), custom feature development (quote provided).</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="question">Q: Can I cancel my subscription anytime?</div>
        <div class="answer">
          <div class="answer-summary"><strong>Answer:</strong> Yes, no long-term contracts: Cancel anytime, pro-rated refunds, data retention for 30 days, one-click reactivation.</div>
          <details>
            <summary>Read full answer</summary>
            <div class="answer-full">
              <p><strong>Cancel Anytime:</strong> Self-serve cancellation in account settings. No phone calls required.</p>
              <p><strong>Pro-rated Refunds:</strong> If you cancel mid-cycle, get refund for unused months.</p>
              <p><strong>Data Retention:</strong> Your formatted figures remain accessible for 30 days after cancellation (in case you change your mind).</p>
              <p><strong>Reactivation:</strong> One click to reactivate if you change your mind.</p>
              <p><strong>Our Promise:</strong> We don't want unhappy customers. If you're not satisfied, we'll make it right or refund you. No questions asked.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
